I am getting very annoyed at reviewers who give recipes 4 forks based on considerable changes they have made to a recipe. As written, this recipe doesn't turn out as expected and lacks flavor and texture. Most of the suggestions involve turning this recipe into a typical one for crab cakes. I also agree with reviewer who said that the mayo/yogurt/sour cream sauce (I used a combo of all three to be safe) is like sour cream with grass in it (and I had a lot left over). I hadn't been a subscriber to Gourmet magazine in its later years, but if this is an example of the types of recipes they printed...

Rating: 3
I made this for my kids and it certainly smells lovely. Being from Nova Scotia, we are very particular about our fish cakes and, due to this, I'm getting a bit p.oed with regards to how they are totally falling apart in the pan. I would follow the other reviewers as to additions and to coating them in flour before frying. If I were to make these again I would really cut the salmon into smaller pieces (maybe minced) in order for cohesion. Nothing more disappointing than it all falling apart in the pan. The taste is good and the dipping sauce is great altho I had to substitute dill for the tarragon...probably better with dill...tarragon is too overpowering if you actually want to TASTE the salmon

