Rating: 4
These are delicious, and the sauce is superb - you must use fresh ingredients for the sauce! I used 1/2 panko and 1/2 regular bread crumbs. I little extra mayonnaise helps things hold together. I probably added garlic, I add it to almost everything. I make a batch of these and pack some for lunch at work, have some for dinner, and I get a few days of meals out of them. That just about satisfies my cravings for them for a little while!

Rating: 3
I'm not a huge salmon fan, but my husband and daughter like it so I tried these today. My two year old devoured them! I cut the salmon into much smaller pieces, used all panko for the bread crumbs, and added the 3T capers, and green onions another reviewer suggested and about 2T mayonnaise. They fell apart a little bit, but not terribly. I made the cakes larger for entree servings. I also left out the lime zest and used about 1T of lemon juice. Since sour cream is much different in Sweden, I used creme fraiche for the sauce and lemon juice instead of lime since that's what I had. Although I'm not so keen on salmon, the fact that my daughter loved these means we'll be having them again for sure.

