Rating: 4
This was an excellent recipe. I got raves from my husband during dinner. I did make some adjustments. I read the suggestions of other reviewers and decided to follow along with their insights. Firstly I had some alaska smoked salmon on hand so I used that to make this dish instead of fresh salmon. 2nd I followed the suggestion of 4 tbsp of mayo, 3 tbsp capers, chop green onions, a dash cayenne, and the juice of 1 lime, I added to the mixture. I also coated the cakes in a dusting of flour before frying. They turned out awesome and did not fall apart at all. The sauce was the perfect compliment. I would think that if you only had canned salmon on hand, that would do nicely in this recipe as well. This recipe is definitely a keeper. Thanks to all the other reviewers for their suggestions. You were spot on!

Rating: 4
My variation on this was delicious! Based on what I remembered from the restaurant where I made salmon cakes, I added some very finely chopped red pepper, celery, and minced garlic, put in some lemon juice in place of the zest, and added about 1/3 cup of mayo, which made the cakes stick together so they're much easier to handle. Served with parsley aioli, and they're delicious! Also good with other flaky fish -- good use for any extra fish in the freezer!

