Rating: 3
Per other cook's suggestions, I made some adjustments and these turned out great. First, forget about the 1/3 in cubes! I cut the salmon into really tiny pieces. I then increased the breadcrumbs to 1 cup, added 2 tblsp minced shallots, 2 tablsp softened cream cheese, 2 tblsp diced green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon celery seed, 2 tblsp tarragon-chive dipping sauce and 1 teaspoon garlic powder. Mixture should be very "damp" but not runny. Also increased the black pepper and made into "burger size" patties. Cooked 'em up with a tblsp of butter in the pan until they were golden (3 minutes on side 1 & 2 minutes on side 2). Served these on toasted buns with a slice of tomato and choice of mayo or the dipping sauce and they were great! Actually trying the same recipe with tuna tonight.

