Like the cook from Pryor, OK I pretty much altered this recipe. On the West Coast of Canada we call them patties, too. I used leftover baked salmon and skipped the breadcrumbs substituting 3/4 cup cooked mashed potatoes. I did not use the dijon or lime, but instead used 1 heaping tsp. of Madras Curry Powder and a good handful of chopped green onion. I needed an extra egg, too. I fried them to a crisp golden brown and served with a choice of bearnaise sauce or homemade Major Grey chutney - Delicious!!

