Rating: 4
I made alot of changes to this .. almost a different dish entirely, but we absolutely loved it. I used salmon, left-over from a previous dinner, that I had pan grilled in garlic, olive oil, and butter. In food processor, I chopped 2 shallots, some green onions, 1/2 green pepper. Then blended in 12 oz softened cream cheese, the salmon, 2 eggs, bread crumbs, some grated romano cheese, couple dashes of jalapeno sauce. When nice and creamy, I poured into a buttered loaf pan and baked at 350 for about 45 minutes. Yummy! Texture of a cheese cake but good strong flavors. For the sauce, I substitued dill for the tarragon, increased the amount of chives, added a dash of garlic powder. This will be a repeat for us!

Rating: 3
I love salmon patties (that is what we call them). However this recipe does need improvments and all the other suggestions are great. I would like to emphasize the baking of the fish to be used or as what we do is fresh pack the fish (jar it) which cooks it in the jar. When you use the fresh pack, you can crumble it easily and add your additional ingredients. Baking the fish will give you the same result. This allows you to form the patties and brown them quickly and easily.

